  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Envelope 2: CCCM, Health and MHPSS, S-NFI, and WASH Response to Support People to People in Internally Displaced Persons (IDP) Sites</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">According to the 2021 South Sudan Humanitarian Needs Overview, most displaced people are expected to remain displaced in 2021, and Bentiu and Naivasha internally displaced persons (IDP) sites and Malakal Protection of Civilian site (PoC) will continue to be refuge for a significant number of IDPs as subnational violence, fragile peace, and a lack of basic services persist in South Sudan. The Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM) priority for this allocation is to continue providing camp management services and site care and maintenance. Under the health sector, IOM is contributing to improve people&#x2019;s access to and utilization of essential healthcare services. Within these efforts, and in line with the priority for integrated quality essential health care services, IOM is providing focused, non-specialized mental health and psychosocial services at the sites. Additionally, IOM continues to coordinate and provide shelter-non-food Item service depending on the needs of the community, as well as integrated, safe, equitable, and dignified access to water, sanitation and hygiene services to IDPs.</narrative>
  </description>
